        <p>
            As read above, activities are the way to switch the cycle. But, how do they work? Activities may have
            different impacts according to the time they can take. There is three groups:
        </p>
        <deflist type="medium">
            <def title="1. Full-day Activities">
                Activities taking a whole day <control>(12h~24h)</control> to being completed: long-distance travels,
                huge quest objectives.
            </def>
            <def title="2. Half-day Activities">
                Activities taking a half-day <control>(6h~12h)</control> to being completed: normal travels, normal
                quest objectives.
            </def>
            <def title="3. Short Activities">
                Activities taking a short time <control>(1h~6h)</control> to being completed: mini-games, environment
                interactions, short quest objectives.
            </def>
        </deflist>
        <p>The <control>displayed time</control> is written as in-game clock.</p>
        <p>
            Moreover, when a player is not doing an activity, the time on their world is passing as fast as real time
            (scale <control>1:1 - 24h/day</control>).
        </p>

